MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: AirAsia to Add Planes, Sime Suit, IOI Profit

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-02-16T00:15:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/malaysia-daybook-airasia-to-add-planes-sime-suit-ioi-profit.html
AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA MK),  Southeast
Asia ’s biggest discount airline, is in talks to buy about 175 of
Airbus SAS’s upgraded A320 jet as it adds short-haul flights
within the region, Chief Executive Officer Tony Fernandes said
in an interview.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Supermax Corp. (SUCB MK) holds analysts and media briefing on
2010 earnings at 10:30 a.m. in Kuala Lumpur.
* Metro Kajang Holdings Bhd. (MKH MK) holds briefing on property
developments at 10:45 a.m. in Kajang.
* IOI Corp. (IOI MK), the palm oil producer, is expected to
announce fiscal second-quarter earnings during the 12:30 p.m.
break.
* Societe Generale de Surveillance is expected to release
Malaysian palm oil export data for Feb. 1-15 after 12:30 a.m.
*  Malaysia  Airports Holdings Bhd. (MAHB MK) to announce fourth-
quarter results at 2 p.m. in Sepang.
* Green Packet Bhd.(GRPB MK) to hold media briefing on 2010
results at 4 p.m. in  Petaling Jaya .  EQUITY PREVIEW:
* Sime Darby Bhd. (SIME MK):  The company confirmed that
Emirates International Energy Services is suing its engineering
division in Dubai. The group hasn’t yet been served with the
suit and isn’t aware of the basis and grounds of the claim, it
said in a statement on its website.
* Century Software Holdings Bhd. (CSHB MK): Malaysia Venture
Capital Management Bhd. said it ceased to be a substantial
shareholder of the company after selling 7 million shares, a
stock filing showed.
* Digistar Corp. (DICB MK): The network services company said it
priced its placement shares at 16 sen each. That’s a 5.9 percent
discount to the stock’s recent market price, it said in an
exchange filing.
* Metro Kajang Holdings Bhd. (MKH MK): The property developer
said it plans to give one new share for every 10 held as part of
a bonus issue. This is to further enhance the marketability and
trading liquidity of the company’s shares, it said in a
statement.
* Multi-Purpose Holdings Bhd. (MPU MK): The Malaysian gaming and
financial services group said preliminary plans to re-list
Magnum Holdings Sdn. have been “placed on hold,” according to
a company statement.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index rose 0.7 percent on
Feb. 14, ahead of yesterday’s market holiday in  Kuala Lumpur .
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 0.2 percent yesterday.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost 0.3 percent yesterday.
* Palm oil April-delivery futures fell 0.6 percent to 3,933
ringgit ($1,289) a metric ton on Feb. 14.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter in Kuala Lumpur at 
